			<p>BLACKOUT (Audio Documentary)</p>
			<p>
				Produced by: Miguel Rodriguez
				Written by: M.C Josephson & Miguel Rodriguez
			</p>
			<p>
				Nine moths and 21 days after its grandiose opening, the modern and highly controversial Science City, the largest research facility in the world, experienced a blackout that not only left its entire night staff in darkness, but also put their lives at serious risk. While there is an open investigation which will determine the future of the overwhelmingly large underground structure, this documentary, composed of audio recordings made by said staff on different devices and a recorded police phone call, chooses not to take sides in the heated debate that surrounds the topic and focuses instead on how those trapped that night coped with the situation.
			</p>
			<p>
				A sociological study, Blackout intentionally leaves out not only all comments by people other than those confined in the building that night, but also any afterthought that they might have had once their predicament was over. The intention is, according to its producer, that the audience “sit down in a dark room and feel for 10 minutes the way that all those unfortunate people felt that night for five hours.”
			</p>
			<p>Running time: 10 minutes.</p>

			<p>Cast: Marcus Frewin-Ridley, Elise Whyte, Kristin Duffy, Paula Brett, and Jon Clemens</p>

			<p>Recordings by: Jon Clemens and Miguel Rodriguez</p>

			<p>Editing and mixing: Miguel Rodriguez</p>
