			<p>EXTRAORDINARY CITIES SERIES: COMPLEX AT THE CENTRE OF THE UNIVERSE (Audio Documentary)</p>
			<p>“Solely through sound, an entire environment, complete with memories and emotions, comes alive.”
					Barry Blesser and Linda Salter, Spaces Speak: Are You Listening?</p>
			<p>
				Produced by: Miguel Rodriguez
				Written by: M.C Josephson & Miguel Rodriguez
			</p>
			<p>
				In this first programme of the Extraordinary Cities Series, journalist Anna Jones takes us on a sound walk through the magnificent Complex at the Centre of the Universe. The city, vertical in nature and built upon a 6-acre rock in the middle of the Pacific Ocean, presents us with a unique soundscape, in which the ceaseless traffic background inherent to most horizontal cities in the world is replaced by the roaring of the ocean from all sides. In her journey, Parks visits both the landmarks of the city, such as the Roof Garden and the Ground Floor Garden, and those places its inhabitants go by daily as part of their routine, such as the lift stations and the residential floors.
			</p>
			<p>
				By exploring cities through their soundscapes, the Extraordinary Cities Series attempts to immerse its audience into the dynamic of a place, its movement and its activities in a way a landscape would not be able to accomplish, giving them a unique auditory first impression that would hopefully encourage further exploration. 
			</p>
			<p>Running time: 10 minutes.</p>

			<p>Cast: Elise Whyte, Paula Brett, Jon Clemens, and Marcus Frewin-Ridley</p>

